{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3b6c21e4-0702-4850-ad60-e0db9a0a562b","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\nHere are the main tools for analyzing `.dmp` files from .NET apps:\n\n**1. `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, recommended)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n```\nUseful commands inside the REPL:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n**2. `lldb` with SOS** (Linux)\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core <your-file.dmp>\n```\nThen: `clrstack`, `pe`, `dso`, etc.\n\n**3. Visual Studio / WinDbg** (Windows)\nOpen the `.dmp` directly; VS will offer \"Debug with Managed Only.\"\n\n---\n\n**Quick triage steps:**\n1. Run `dotnet-dump analyze your.dmp`\n2. Type `pe` to print the exception that caused the crash\n3. Type `clrstack` to see the stack trace\n4. If no exception, check `threads` and inspect each thread's stack\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and start analyzing a specific file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5bfe136b-5849-4b35-a994-058a0d6afc77","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":474,"requestId":"ABC8:24FEAD:1473817:16F02AB:6A0672CD"},"id":"a9c1b5d4-1594-4189-81ad-64480859d029","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:11:54.804Z","parentId":"e797d916-44f3-4605-94fd-c55e3d743d88"}
